 for all. It stresses the need to intervene early to combat child poverty and break the vicious cycles that perpetuate poverty and disadvantage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGenerationsxEconomic conditions. 0aPoverty. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Poverty & Homelessness.2bisacsh1 aFrazer, Hugh, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGuio, Anne-Catherine, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311119679440uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447370611?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447370611zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447370611/original  a978-3-11-119679-4 Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA